The paper proposes a new approach for early prediction of vital signs using generative boosting via LSTM networks. This involves both generative and predictive models, which are trained using a diverse range of benchmark models. The paper also uses a mutual information based clustering algorithm to select a more representative dataset for training the generative model. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
